OL,3,CRoyal Marine recruit given 'thrashing'
OL,4,Con the night before he died, inquest
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe night before he died, on 11 June
OL,8,F2021, Connor and the other new
OL,9,Frecruits in his troop had undergone a
OL,10,Fphysical punishment of press-ups,
OL,11,Flasting nearly an hour.
OL,13,FFellow recruit Able Seaman Chris Lee
OL,14,Ftold the hearing in Exeter, although
OL,15,Fhe could not remember precisely how
OL,16,Flong the so called "thrashing" was, it
OL,17,Fwas "very significantly more" than the
OL,18,Frecommended fifteen minutes given for
OL,19,Fsanctions.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
